<TITLE> India on alert after restaurant blast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 INDIA, Feb 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)--- Indian police step up security after the attack on a restaurant in Pune popular with foreign tourists. India's interior minister has been taking a first hand look at the scene of Saturday's bomb blast at a busy restaurant in Pune. Palaniappan Chidambaram says the motive for the attack that killed nine people wounded more than 50 others is so far a mystery. But he says police were aware that other sites in the city were allegedly surveyed by a US man accused of scouting for targets for the Mumbai attackers in 2008. SOUNDBITE: Palaniappan Chidambaran, Indian interior minister, saying (English): "The Chabad House was surveyed by David Headley. The police were sensitised that the Chabad House was a target." As the wounded came to terms with their ordeal in hospital police were still trying to establish who was behind the attack. The German Bakery restaurant was popular with Jewish and European visitors. The bombing happened a day after India and Pakistan agreed to launch top-level talks. A four-year peace process between the two was suspended by India after the Mumbai bombings it blamed on Pakistani militants. It's the first major attack since then and police across much of India have stepped up security checks in respo
